{"questionId":"27869","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An artificial ski slope can be modelled as a triangular prism, as shown in the diagram.&nbsp;Rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABCD</mtext></math> is horizontal, and rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CDEF</mtext></math> is vertical.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/8e62c1d5a225f2ad1e164c8ce6ed51d863814c2c.png\"></p>\n<p>The maximum height of the ski slope, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CF</mtext></math>, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn></math> metres and the steepest angle of the&nbsp;ski slope, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext><mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext></math>, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>[BF]</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>21</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mtext>BF</mtext></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BF</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>47</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>47</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4372</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27869","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the length of [BF].","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}